pson illustrates how these radical Muslims are forming a community dedicated to creative reinterpretations of their religion, critical questioning of established norms, expansive inclusion of those who are queer in various ways, and the creation of different religious futures. Muslims on the Margins is a powerful account of how Muslims are forging new traditions and setting precedents for a more inclusive community— one that is engaged with tradition, but not beholden to it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aMuslim gaysxSocial conditions. 0aMuslim gayszNorth AmericaxSocial conditions. 0aMuslimszNon-Islamic countriesxSocial conditions. 0aMuslimszNorth AmericaxSocial conditions. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh  aIslam.  aMuslims.  adiscursive futurism.  aethnography.  alanguage.  aqueer.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075163540uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479814374.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479814374423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479814374/original  a978-3-11-075163-5  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK